'''Gildor''' roughly translates as "Star-lord" in [[Sindarin]] (from ''[[gil]]'', "star, bright spark" and ''[[taur]]'', "lord") and can refer to:

* [[Gildor (outlaw)]], one of [[Barahir]]'s [[XII Bëorings|outlaws]] in the [[First Age]].
* '''[[Gildor]] Inglorion, a [[Noldor]]in [[Elves|Elf]] encountered by [[Frodo Baggins|Frodo]] and [[Samwise Gamgee|Sam]] in ''[[The Fellowship of the Ring]]''.'''
